), M.P. for Kidderminster 1852–59, and for Calne 1859–68. Lowe had supported Palmerston’s foreign policy and anticipated a cabinet post in his new govt., formed 31 May, but was given a noncabinet post in the privy council, as vice president of the council for education. turned up, at Albert-GateGate into Hyde Park, named after Prince Albert, built in 1841. the other night, coming out of the Park; very fresh;—no doubt, looking forth with much more interest into all that; whh is Lowe’s mill, if it be not even his kirk too!TC is playing with the Scots saying “make a kirk and a mill of it”; it can mean making the best of it, do as one likes with it, make what one will of it, implying some indifference about the result; see 
